# Flutter TaskFlow - Quick Start Guide

## Overview
This guide provides step-by-step instructions to get the TaskFlow Flutter application up and running in your `~/src/repos/` directory.

## Prerequisites âœ…

Based on your existing setup:
- âœ… Flutter SDK 3.29.3 installed
- âœ… Dart SDK 3.9.2 configured  
- âœ… VS Code with Flutter/Dart extensions
- âœ… Development environment validated

## 1. Project Setup (5 minutes)

### Initialize the Project
```bash
cd ~/src/repos/
flutter create flutter_task_manager --project-name task_flow --platforms android,ios,web
cd flutter_task_manager
```

### Verify Installation
```bash
flutter doctor -v
flutter --version
```

Expected output:
```
Flutter 3.29.3 â€¢ channel stable
Dart 3.9.2 â€¢ DevTools 2.37.3
```

## 2. Dependencies Installation (3 minutes)

### Core Dependencies
```bash
# State Management & Architecture
flutter pub add flutter_bloc provider get_it dartz freezed_annotation

# Networking & Data
flutter pub add dio json_annotation hive hive_flutter shared_preferences

# UI & Navigation
flutter pub add go_router cached_network_image flutter_svg

# Development Tools
flutter pub add --dev build_runner json_serializable freezed flutter_lints mockito bloc_test
```

### Verify Dependencies
```bash
flutter pub get
flutter pub deps
```

## 3. Project Structure Setup (2 minutes)

### Create Directory Structure
```bash
# Create feature-first architecture
mkdir -p lib/core/{config,errors,network,storage,utils}
mkdir -p lib/features/authentication/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/features/tasks/{data/{models,repositories,datasources},domain/{entities,repositories,usecases},presentation/{bloc,pages,widgets}}
mkdir -p lib/shared/{presentation/{widgets,themes,routing},utils}
```

### Verify Structure
```bash
tree lib/ -d
```

## 4. Core Configuration (10 minutes)

### Create Analysis Options
```bash
cat > analysis_options.yaml << 'EOF'
include: package:flutter_lints/flutter.yaml

analyzer:
  exclude:
    - "**/*.g.dart"
    - "**/*.freezed.dart"
    - "build/**"

linter:
  rules:
    prefer_single_quotes: true
    prefer_const_constructors: true
    avoid_print: true
EOF
```

### Create App Configuration
```bash
cat > lib/core/config/app_config.dart << 'EOF'
class AppConfig {
  static const String appName = 'TaskFlow';
  static const String appVersion = '1.0.0';
  static const bool isDebugMode = true;

  // API Configuration
  static const String baseUrl = 'https://api.taskflow.dev';
  static const int connectTimeout = 30000;
  static const int receiveTimeout = 30000;

  // Feature flags
  static const bool enableAnalytics = true;
  static const bool enableCrashReporting = false;
}
EOF
```

### Create Core Failures
```bash
cat > lib/core/errors/failures.dart << 'EOF'
abstract class Failure {
  final String message;
  const Failure(this.message);
}

class NetworkFailure extends Failure {
  const NetworkFailure([super.message = 'Network error occurred']);
}

class CacheFailure extends Failure {
  const CacheFailure([super.message = 'Cache error occurred']);
}

class ServerFailure extends Failure {
  const ServerFailure([super.message = 'Server error occurred']);
}

class ValidationFailure extends Failure {
  const ValidationFailure([super.message = 'Validation error occurred']);
}
EOF
```

## 5. Basic App Theme (5 minutes)

### Create App Theme
```bash
cat > lib/shared/presentation/themes/app_theme.dart << 'EOF'
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

class AppTheme {
  static ThemeData get lightTheme {
    return ThemeData(
      useMaterial3: true,
      colorScheme: ColorScheme.fromSeed(
        seedColor: const Color(0xFF6366F1),
        brightness: Brightness.light,
      ),
      appBarTheme: const AppBarTheme(
        centerTitle: true,
        elevation: 0,
      ),
    );
  }

  static ThemeData get darkTheme {
    return ThemeData(
      useMaterial3: true,
      colorScheme: ColorScheme.fromSeed(
        seedColor: const Color(0xFF6366F1),
        brightness: Brightness.dark,
      ),
      appBarTheme: const AppBarTheme(
        centerTitle: true,
        elevation: 0,
      ),
    );
  }
}
EOF
```

## 6. Main Application Setup (5 minutes)

### Update main.dart
```bash
cat > lib/main.dart << 'EOF'
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_bloc/flutter_bloc.dart';
import 'package:get_it/get_it.dart';
import 'package:shared_preferences/shared_preferences.dart';

import 'core/config/app_config.dart';
import 'shared/presentation/themes/app_theme.dart';

final sl = GetIt.instance;

Future<void> main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  await initializeDependencies();
  runApp(const TaskFlowApp());
}

Future<void> initializeDependencies() async {
  // External dependencies
  final sharedPreferences = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
  sl.registerLazySingleton(() => sharedPreferences);
}

class TaskFlowApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const TaskFlowApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: AppConfig.appName,
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: AppConfig.isDebugMode,
      theme: AppTheme.lightTheme,
      darkTheme: AppTheme.darkTheme,
      home: const HomePage(),
    );
  }
}

class HomePage extends StatelessWidget {
  const HomePage({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text(AppConfig.appName),
      ),
      body: const Center(
        child: Column(
          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
          children: [
            Icon(
              Icons.check_circle,
              size: 64,
              color: Colors.green,
            ),
            SizedBox(height: 16),
            Text(
              'TaskFlow is Ready!',
              style: TextStyle(fontSize: 24, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
            ),
            SizedBox(height: 8),
            Text(
              'Your Flutter development environment is working perfectly.',
              textAlign: TextAlign.center,
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
EOF
```

## 7. Verification & Testing (3 minutes)

### Run Analysis
```bash
flutter analyze
```
Expected: "No issues found!"

### Run the Application
```bash
# For mobile (if you have a device/emulator)
flutter run

# For web
flutter run -d chrome

# For desktop (Linux)
flutter run -d linux
```

### Run Tests
